<h1>🧊 M002 Week 5 — Mini Cube Puzzle</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Mini Cube Puzzle · <strong>Course:</strong> Maze Madness · <strong>Level:</strong> Advanced · <strong>Time:</strong> about 55 minutes</p>
<p>Finish the mini cube. Keep the starter going: add <strong>2 more conditionals</strong> with <strong>one <code>OR</code></strong>, fill the cube, then break a hole in the <strong>top</strong> and climb out.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Write what happens.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">for i in range(5):
    agent.place(BLOCK)
    agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What shape is left behind? How long is it?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-python">if on_edge or on_top_layer:
    agent.place(BLOCK)
else:
    pass  # leave empty
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only one condition must be true. Which spots get a block? Which stay empty?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Trace 👣</h2>
<pre><code class="language-python">for layer in range(3):
    fill_layer()
    agent.move(UP, 1)
if agent.detect(BLOCK, UP):
    # break above, then climb
    agent.move(UP, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>How many layers fill? Where does the agent end up? Is there still a block above it?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

